# E-Commerce Dashboard Validation Project

## Overview

This project demonstrates an end-to-end QA validation workflow for an e-commerce analytics dashboard.

The objective was to verify that dashboard metrics matched source database records and that business rules were implemented correctly.

## Skills Demonstrated

- SQL Validation
- Test Case Design
- Requirements Analysis
- Defect Investigation
- Root Cause Analysis
- Regression Testing
- QA Documentation
- Release Sign-Off

## Business Metrics Validated

- Total Orders
- Revenue
- Active Customers
- Refund Totals
- Top Selling Products

## Key Deliverables

- Requirements Traceability Matrix (RTM)
- SQL Validation Queries
- Bug Report
- Retest Results
- Final QA Recommendation

## Project Document

See:
**Ecommerce_Dashboard_Validation_Project.pdf**

## Project Highlights

This project simulates a real-world QA engagement where dashboard calculations were validated against source database records. A high-severity revenue discrepancy was identified, investigated, documented, retested, and resolved before production release.

## Outcome

All requirements were successfully validated, defects were resolved, and the dashboard was approved for production deployment.
